Vietson,<br><br>
You ask a very difficult question for which there is no definitive answer.<br><br>
The history of Vietnam since WW2 seems to be one betrayal after another. <br><br>
The Vietnam War, the US portion, embodied betrayal, not only to the people of Vietnam in the end, but betrayal to those US soldiers who fought there. The conflicting sherade of US Government policies, the mood of the people of the United States, and personal political agendas of government officials on all sides, contributed to the catastrophy as we now see it, hopefully through the eyes of wisdom that time has given us.<br><br>
I feel that there are still elements in this country who would rather see the Vietnam experience go away. Other political agendas are at work now, as well. I do not know what the chances are for enhanced assistance to refugee Vietnamese, but unless there is pressure from Congress, I  do not see the US Government becomming suddenly embued with altruism. <br><br>
I personally feel it should be otherwise.<br><br>
 
